Diagnosis.
This species can be recognized by the combination of the following characters: medium to large sized wasp, mesosoma densely and coarsely punctate and interspaces raised to form reticulation, female metasomal sterna with longitudinal ridges (
Fig. 37
), coloration of metasoma ranging from entirely black to black with extensive orange markings on T1–T5, and clypeus of male entirely black or almost black with very reduced yellow lateral lines (
Fig. 38
).
